column5: Fairly early ice up here in the Vermilion Bay area.Clarks got there ice shacks out yesterday on around 5 inches of fresh ice on Edward Lake{Indian Lake Chain}As usual first ice walleyes didn't disappoint.Lots of walleyes in a couple of hours.
Looks great! Such photos awaken in me appetite
What is the purpose of the boards that are sticking up from each shack? to hold up an electric line to a generator (had to ask).
They are the poles for the electricity.Couple more poles will be put up from shore yet to run the wires for the lights.Both shacks are heated with propane.
Sissy fishing. Exactly what I need!
What??? You have ice fishing in TN?!?!? Pooch
I like being a sissy.warm is nice.6
